<br>
So, are movies getting dumber? The only other option I have is that I'm getting smarter and I can now see how silly movies really are, but I really doubt anyone will agree that I'm getting any smarter so ... yeah .... are movies getting dumber?<br>
<br>
Perhaps dumber is not the complete correct term. Perhaps 'Complete formless mess' is a better term. Most action movies have the following plot --- Begining, crap happens, ending just pulled out of the ether happens---- <br>
<br>
For example 'Men in Black II' ... allright ... bad guy shows up looking some silly item of power, crap happens, Tommy Lee Jones suddenly remembers he had a plan going on, despite the fact that he had been brainwashed in the last movie and had no expectations of getting called back into the job. Oh yeah, and some girl who barely shows up during the movie happens to be an alien princess and saves the world by taking the stupid magical trinket with her. So yeah, a complete mess of a movie. <br>
<br>
Or the Phantom ... yeah I know, horrible movie... easily on the top 5 worst movies I have seen .... with Billy Zane in them  ... .about comics .... in a Friday. Anyway, one bad guy who was the head of some secret organization wants some magic trinkets. Dumb stuff happens and the Phantom and the bad guy reach some island where the secret organization lives, except that the people in the island, who were members of this secret organization, didn't know about the organization outside the island, and the bad guy didn't even know the island existed ... so ... what the hell? I dunno. Stupid horrible mess of a movie.<br>
<br>
That didn't happen before! None of the Indiana Jones movies is Shakespeare, but at least most of the plot makes sense.  <br>
<br>
So yeah, are movies getting dumber since the 90s? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#111111><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/blucifer.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hg@lucifer>HG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFF99>(10/14/03 2:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Are movies getting dumber?</span><hr size=1> I don't think movies are getting dumber.<br>
